HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO US, HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO US!
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    They may not look it but this year the 1st St Margarets Scout Group
    is 100 years old. It all kicked off on Monday 24th November 1919
    when a local man, Mr Arthur William Laurence, came to the
    conclusion that the only thing St Margarets needed to turn it
    into an earthly paradise- all the other necessary attributes being
    in place - was a Scout Troop, so he started one. He cunningly
    called it the "1st St Margarets" and himself, being the leader,
    "Skipper" The story has it that the first meetings were held under
    a gaslight on a street corner.

